.slide{
    .title{Welcome to slidedown}
    .body{
        <h1>A minimal example demonstrating all directives</h1>
        <p>This presentation showcases every available .directive{} in slidedown.</p>
        <p>Navigate: Arrow keys or click</p>
    }
}

.slide{
    .title{Text Formatting}
    .body{
        <h2>Text Formatting Aliases</h2>

        <p>.bf{Bold text} produces bold (strong) text</p>

        <p>.em{Emphasized text} produces italic (emphasis) text</p>

        <p>.tt{Teletype text} produces monospace text</p>

        <p>.code{function_name()} produces inline code</p>

        <p>.underline{Underlined text} produces underlined text</p>

        <p>Mix them: .bf{Bold with .em{italic inside}}</p>
    }
}

.slide{
    .title{Progressive Reveals}
    .body{
        <h2>Progressive Bullet Points</h2>
        <p>Use .o{} for progressive reveal bullets:</p>

        .o{First bullet appears}
        .o{Second bullet appears on next click}
        .o{Third bullet appears after that}
        .o{Each .o{} creates a new reveal}
        .o{Perfect for step-by-step explanations}
    }
}

.slide{
    .title{Typewriter Effect}
    .body{
        <h2>Character-by-Character Reveal</h2>
        <p>The .typewriter{} behavior creates animated text:</p>

        .typewriter{
This text will appear
character by character
with a typing animation effect
        }
    }
}

.slide{
    .title{ASCII Art - Figlet Fonts}
    .body{
        <h2>ASCII Art with <code>.font-NAME&lbrace;&rbrace;</code></h2>

        .font-standard{slidedown}

        .font-slant{Slant Font}

        .font-banner{BANNER}
    }
}

.slide{
    .title{More ASCII Art Fonts}
    .body{
        .font-doom{DOOM}

        .font-basic{Basic Style}
    }
}

.slide{
    .title{Cowsay Speech Bubbles}
    .body{
        <h2>ASCII Characters with <code>.cowpy-NAME&lbrace;&rbrace;</code></h2>

        .cowpy-cow{Moo! I'm a cow saying hello from slidedown!}
    }
}

.slide{
    .title{More Cowsay Characters}
    .body{
        .cowpy-tux{Hello from Tux the penguin!}

        .cowpy-dragon{Dragons can speak too!}
    }
}

.slide{
    .title{Combining Directives}
    .body{
        <h2>Directives Can Be Nested</h2>

        .o{.bf{Bold} text in a bullet}
        .o{.em{Emphasized} text in a bullet}
        .o{.code{code()} inside a bullet}

        <p>Mix structural and formatting directives for rich content.</p>
    }
}

.slide{
    .title{Advanced Nesting}
    .body{
        <h2>Complex Directive Combinations</h2>

        <p>Typewriter effect inside bullets:</p>

        .o{.typewriter{First step types out when revealed}}
        .o{.typewriter{Second step types out on next click}}
        .o{.typewriter{Final step types out last}}

        <p>Creates progressive reveals with typing animation.</p>
    }
}

.slide{
    .title{Raw HTML Support}
    .body{
        <h2>HTML Works Alongside Directives</h2>

        <ul>
            <li>Standard HTML tags work fine</li>
            <li>Use directives for special effects</li>
            <li>Use HTML for standard structure</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Best practice: .bf{Use directives for slidedown features},
        HTML for standard document structure.</p>
    }
}

.slide{
    .style{background: black; color: lightgreen;}
    .title{Style Directive Examples}
    .body{
        <h2>Custom Styling with .style{}</h2>

        .o{This slide has black background and light green text}
        .o{Set with <code>.style&lbrace;background: black; color: lightgreen;&rbrace;</code>}
        .o{The .style&lbrace;&rbrace; directive applies CSS to the slide}

        <p>You can use any valid CSS properties.</p>
    }
}

.slide{
    .style{background: linear-gradient(to right, #2c3e50, #3498db); color: white; font-family: monospace;}
    .title{More Style Examples}
    .body{
        <h2>Gradient Background + Monospace Font</h2>

        <p>This slide demonstrates:</p>
        .o{Linear gradient background}
        .o{White text color}
        .o{Monospace font family}

        <p style="font-size: 1.2em; border: 2px solid white; padding: 10px;">
            The .style&lbrace;&rbrace; directive is powerful!
        </p>
    }
}

.slide{
    .title{Summary}
    .body{
        <h2>All Available Directives</h2>

        .o{.bf{Structure:} <code>.slide&lbrace;&rbrace;</code>, <code>.title&lbrace;&rbrace;</code>, <code>.body&lbrace;&rbrace;</code>}
        .o{.bf{Format:} <code>.bf&lbrace;&rbrace;</code>, <code>.em&lbrace;&rbrace;</code>, <code>.tt&lbrace;&rbrace;</code>, <code>.code&lbrace;&rbrace;</code>, <code>.underline&lbrace;&rbrace;</code>}
        .o{.bf{Effects:} <code>.typewriter&lbrace;&rbrace;</code>, <code>.o&lbrace;&rbrace;</code>}
        .o{.bf{ASCII Art:} <code>.font-NAME&lbrace;&rbrace;</code>, <code>.cowpy-NAME&lbrace;&rbrace;</code>}
        .o{.bf{Nesting:} Directives compose freely}

        <br>
        <p>.em{Now you know all the directives in slidedown!}</p>
    }
}
